survey_response.review_text: I visited Dr.Krishna Prasanna in Aksha hospital, Nallagandla. She is very cool and friendly in discussing the health condition of mine. I had anterior central placenta previa till the end. And i had GDM. I had brown discharge twice during my pregnancy in 28th week and 33rd week. She was personally in touch with me on phone and suggested medication accordingly. I had heavy vaginal bleeding in my 35th week of gestation. She arranged everything and asked me to admit in the care hospital (as she is working in care and due to the pregnancy complications i had) and delivered the baby via emergency c section. I strongly recommend her for consultation.

Dr.p.krishna set a in house i mean community based visit for the sake of residents for various menstrual problems in women. That time i consulted with her with my post menopause/abdominal pelvic scan . Later I came to know that we can have an appointment of the particular doctor at care hospitals  high tech city. Immediately I got done with all my reports and she suggested to go for biopsy as the endometrial line is got thickened by 10 mm which is not good for my age of 66 years. So by the way the biopsy shows negative. Dr. P.Krishna asked me to go for mri and oncology suggestion .
She guided me well advance in getting further surgery and is very concerned about me also. Though I am not her patient in the later stages she visited me advised me for further well being. Thank you for the doctor 🙏

I was consulting with Dr Krishna for my pregnancy. Dr was very friendly and was explaining things well. And she was very dedicated and helpful at the delivery time. Thank you so much.   Also I had hyperthyroidism for which Dr Krishna provided guidances time to time.  I would recommend her  for any maternity related consultation.

I consulted Dr Krishna for PCOS problem and pregnancy related. She is such a wonderful doctor i have ever met in my life. She truly cares for her patients and remembers entire case of the patient from inch to inch. She is always ready to walk that extra mile to give the best possible treatment and is just a phone call / message away in case of emergency. I really admire her for being so generous and caring. She was more than a doctor to me throughout my pregnancy journey and gave me the best suggestions whenever it was needed the most for me.  I never thought that I can recover from a C section so quickly and I wholeheartedly give that credit to the doctor for that. I can't thank her enough for being such a caring doctor and wonderful human being. After my surgery she has become favourite doctor to my mom and in law as well :)

I visited Dr Krishna prasanna  mam regarding my mother health issue about overian cyst surgery she have taken care of  my mother very well she treated very well
This is the time to  express my sincere gratitude to  Dr Krishna mam
Actually, my mother is very afraid of doctors & hospitals your are very friendly with the patients 
My mother believed in you a lot 
Mom felt very happy  for your treatment  and your way of  talking with patients and showing care .

Thankyou so much ma'am 🙏🏻🙏💗

My 2nd pregnancy (high risk) journey started with complications and so I was quite worried about continuing with it. However, Krishna Prasanna Ma'am always had my back at each and every stage of pregnancy. Now, I am a happy mom to a healthy 2 month old all thanks to her.
She cares so much about her patients that she remembers patients cases better than patients themselves.

I visited Dr Krishna for my issue with cervical polypectomy. She was patient and diligent in her clinical examination. She is one of the few Doctors i have seen, recommending an outpatient procedure rather than jumping to complicated and expensive surgeries. I got my procedure done with her which was smooth and painless. Thank you Dr Krishna.

She very friendly and listened all the issues and explained each issue in detail.. very polite understand the feelling of patient and treat according to it... I am very satisfied with the behavior and treatment given to my wife during last quarter of her pregnancy.... then whe  we met her... I highly recommend to visist her if you need gyno....

More importantly, she does not ask you to re-do the tests and scans, had you done it in your home town saving you not only money but also time and effort.
